{"lemma":"كَما","slug":"كَما","root":"ك","root_slug":"ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ك","pos":"CONJ","pos_camel":"conj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37207"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%85%D8%A7"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"truffles, Pezizaceae (syn. Terfeziaceae)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic attested in Jewish Palestinian Aramaic כמהה (kamhā) and ܟܝܡܐ (kīmā), from Akkadian 𒌑𒅗𒀪𒈠𒌓 (/⁠kamʾtu⁠/)."},"ipa":["/ka.maʔ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37207","headword_ar":"كَمَاَ","root":"kmA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo'N","text_ar":"كَمْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AkmA^","text_ar":"اكما","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed"},{"kind":"text","text":"people"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the truffles called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo'","text_ar":"كَمْء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamiy^a","text_ar":"كَمِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamaA^N","text_ar":"كَمَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He walked barefoot, and had no shoes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sandals;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiYa walamo takuno Ealayohi naEolN","text_ar":"حَفِىَ وَلَمْ تَكُنْ عَلَيْهِ نَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (accord. to some copies of the S, on the authority of Ks, and so in the L: or, accord. to the K, and an excellent copy of the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiYa waEalayohi naEolN","text_ar":"حَفِىَ وَعَلَيْهِ نَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which may signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became thin in the feet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from much walking,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though wearing shoes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sandals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamaA^N","text_ar":"كَمَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the foot is the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qasaTN","text_ar":"قَسَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [i. e., the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being naturally stiff in the tendons"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamiy^ato","text_ar":"كَمِيَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(his foot, S, A, K, or hand, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became much cracked"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) Also written in a copy of the A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kmA^t","text_ar":"كمات"},{"kind":"text","text":"; app. by a mistake of the transcriber. (TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamiy^a Eani AlA^axobaAri","text_ar":"كَمِيَ عَنِ الاَخْبَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo'N","text_ar":"كَمْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was ignorant of, and understood not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minded not, the news."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["Th","S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%83%D9%85%D8%A7/","headword_ar":"كما","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_21","lexicon_en":"Muḥammad al-Fattinī, Majmaʿ Biḥār al-Anwār fī Gharāʾib al-Tanzīl wa Laṭāʾif al-Akhbār (d. 1578 CE)","lexicon_ar":"مجمع بحار الأنوار للفَتِّنيّ","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=35450#3349f5","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">[كما]</span><span> نه: فيه: إنه مر على أبواب دور متسفلة، فقال: \"اكموها\"، أي استروها لئلا تقع عيون الناس عليها، والكمو: الستر، وروى: أكيموها، أي ارفعوها لئلا يهجم السيل عليها، من الكومة: الرملة الشمرفة. وفيه: للدابة ثلاث خرجات ثم \"تنكمي\"، أي تستتر. ومنه قيل للشجاع: كمي، لأنه استتر بالدرع، والدابة دابة الأرض من أشراط الساعة. ومنه ح: فجئته \"فانكمي\" مني ثم ظهر، وجمع الكمي الكماة. ش: هو بضم كاف، جمع كمي- بفتحها وكسر ميم وشدة ياء. نه: وح: من حلف بملة- إلى: \"كما\" قال- مر في ح. وفيه: \"كما\" ترون القمر ليلة البدر، التشبيه للرؤية وهو فعل الرائي لا للمرئي أي ترون رؤية ينزاح منها الشك. ن: \"كما\" صليت على إبراهيم. وجه التشبيه مع أنه أفضل من إبراهيم أن ذلك قبل علمه بذلك أو سأل دوامه إلى يوم الدين وأن يجعل له لسان صدق في الآخرين أو سأله لا له وأمته- وقد مر في ص. باب كن</span>"}]}}